====Usage notes====
Traditionally, some commentators have objected to the use of "however" at the start of a sentence in the sense of "nevertheless", but in practice this is widely accepted.

The use of a comma before "however" in the sense of "nevertheless", as in "She wanted to go, however she decided against it", is an error, equivalent to using "however" as a conjunction (see below). Compare the correct sentence "She wanted to go, but she decided against it", which uses a true conjunction "but".

